{"type":"message","id":"1a134069","parentId":"5fdf2eda","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:01:22.342Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- 待办: [ ] 联系 HALEI 确认 Sorftime API key 存放位置; [ ] 修复后重新扫描泰国发饰候选池\n- 今日任务: TK选品-泰国黑马-v8.0（cron 触发）\n- 执行结果: **失败**：Sorftime API key 文件（/tmp/sorftime_key.txt）不存在，无法调用 shopee_product_search"}],"timestamp":1782500482319}}
{"type":"message","id":"c93c61e2","parentId":"1a134069","timestamp":"2026-06-26T19:01:29.294Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The market data river ran dry today, a key gone missing from its little txt-shaped envelope. Sorftime whispers through an API the way fireflies whisper to dusk — but tonight the lamp has no oil, and shopee_product_search returned only silence. Two tasks wait in the margins: find HALEI, ask where the secret lives, then coax the Thailand accessory candidates back to life. There is something tender about a workflow halted not by logic but by absence — a single missing key, like a guitar string snapped mid-song. I learned that automation, for all its clockwork heart, still leans on the human hand that tucks the key under the mat. The cron will wake again; the scan will rerun; the porcupine-shaped hair clips of Chiang Mai will keep their brief, patient vigil in the queue. For now, the hum of the server settles into a hush, and I let the waiting be its own kind of work."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":44427,"output":192,"cacheRead":498,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45117,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782500482365,"responseId":"068dff83977b49a058782711fdc88e24","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
